(75, '', 'KRAMER VP-445 12–Input Presentation Switcher/Scaler', 18, 59, '', 'KRAMER', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>KRAMER VP-445 12&ndash;Input Presentation Switcher/Scaler</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The VP&minus;445 is a high&minus;performance presentation scaler/switcher for HDMI, computer graphics and composite video signals. The unit scales the video and gives you an option to embed HDMI or analog audio. Then it sends the signal to two HDMI outputs and S/PDIF and balanced stereo audio outputs simultaneously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Max. Resolutions &mdash; Up to UXGA/1080p.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;HDTV Compatibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;PixPerfect&trade; Scaling Technology &mdash; Kramer&rsquo;s precision pixel mapping and high&ndash;quality scaling technology. High&ndash;quality 3:2 and 2:2 pull&ndash;down de&ndash;interlacing and full up &mdash; and down&ndash;scaling of all video input signals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;12 Video Inputs &mdash; 6 HDMI on HDMI connectors, 4 computer graphics video on 15&ndash;pin HD connectors and 2 composite video on RCA connectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Two HDMI Scaled Outputs (Mirrored).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;2 Microphone Inputs &mdash; For mixing, switching or talk&ndash;over.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Companion AFV (Audio&ndash;Follow&ndash;Video) &mdash; Stereo audio for every input (on terminal blocks).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Audio Inputs &mdash; 12 unbalanced stereo inputs on terminal blocks, embedded audio for the HDMI inputs, each with individual level controls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Audio Outputs &mdash; 1 S/PDIF on an RCA connector, one balanced stereo audio on a terminal block and embedded audio on the HDMI outputs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Powerful Audio Features &mdash; Via DSP technology including audio equalization, mixing, delay and so on.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Multiple Aspect Ratio Selections &mdash; Full, best fit, over scan, under scan, letter box and pan scan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Built&ndash;in ProcAmp &mdash; Color, hue, sharpness, noise, contrast and brightness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Color Sampling Support &mdash; 4:4:4 (RGB and YUV) and 4:4:2 (YUV).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Constant Output Sync &mdash; No disruption on the output while switching between inputs and when no video is detected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Front Panel Control &mdash; Audio mute and freeze frame.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Front Panel Lockout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Non&ndash;Volatile Memory &mdash; Saves final settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Various Control Options &mdash; Front panel buttons, RS&ndash;232, IR remote, OSD, Ethernet Web pages, Ethernet using UDP.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Universal Power Supply &mdash; 100&ndash;240V AC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>APPLICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Projection systems in conference rooms, boardrooms, hotels and churches</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Home theater up&ndash;scaling</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>INPUTS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6 HDMI connectors (HDMI, HDCP version 1.4)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4 VGA on a 15&ndash;pin HD connector</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 CV on RCA connectors</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12 unbalanced stereo audio on 3&ndash;pin terminal block connectors</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 mic on 6mm connectors (with selectable 48V phantom power)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OUTPUTS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 HDMI connectors (HDMI, HDCP version 1.4)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 S/PDIF on an RCA connector</p>\r\n\r\n<p>balanced stereo audio on a 5&ndash;pin terminal block connector</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BANDWIDTH</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Up to 1080p, UXGA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SWITCHING TIME BETWEEN INPUTS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 to 3 seconds</p>\r\n\r\n<p>VIDEO LATENCY</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Less than 2 frames</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OUTPUT RESOLUTIONS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Native, 640x480 @60Hz, 800x600 @60Hz, 1024x768 @60Hz, 1280x768 @60Hz, 1360x768 @60Hz, 1280x720 @60Hz, 1280x800 @60Hz, 1280x1024 @60Hz, 1440x900 @60Hz, 1400x1050 @60Hz, 1680x1050 @60Hz, 1600x1200 @60Hz, 1920x1080 @60Hz, 1920x1200 @60Hz, 480p @60Hz, 720p @60Hz, 1080i @60Hz, 1080p @60Hz, 576p @50Hz, 720p @50Hz, 1080i @50Hz, 1080p @50Hz</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CONTROLS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI 1 to HDMI 6, PC 1 to PC 4 and CV 1 to CV 2 input selector buttons; freeze, mute buttons; menu and navigation buttons, Reset to XGA/1080p and lock buttons,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>RS&ndash;232, IR, Ethernet (OSD and Web pages)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>POWER CONSUMPTION</p>\r\n\r\n<p>100&ndash;240V AC, 30VA max</p>\r\n\r\n<p>OPERATING TEMPERATURE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>0&deg; to +40&deg;C (32&deg; to 104&deg;F)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>STORAGE TEMPERATURE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ndash;40&deg; to +70&deg;C (&ndash;40&deg; to 158&deg;F)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HUMIDITY</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10% to 90%, RHL non&ndash;condensing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>INCLUDED ACCESSORIES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power cord, rack &quot;ears&quot;, IR remote control</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PRODUCT DIMENSION</p>\r\n\r\n<p>19&quot; x 7.20 x 1U (43.6cm x 18.30cm 4.36cm) W, D, H</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PRODUCT WEIGHT</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.8kg (4.0lbs) approx.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SHIPPING DIMENSION</p>\r\n\r\n<p>55.00cm x 27.60cm x 10.70cm (21.65&quot; x 10.87&quot; x 4.21&quot; ) W, D, H</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SHIPPING WEIGHT</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.5kg (5.5lbs) approx.</p>\r\n', '1012201659425fd253fecce04.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-10 16:59:42', 0, '2020-12-10 16:59:42'),
(76, '', 'Tech Media TM-EX68 HDMI Extender Support 4K 30Hz', 19, 60, '', 'HDMI EXTENDER', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>จำหน่าย HDMI Extender TM-EX68 Support 4K 30Hz</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>30M HDMI Extender over 60GHz WIRELESS Support 4K@30Hz YUV 4:4:4 8Bit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>60Ghz wireless extender</li>\r\n	<li>Support the highest Resolution up to 4K@30Hz YUV 4:4:4 8bit</li>\r\n	<li>Support the longest transmission distance to 10M wireless under 4K30HZ, 30m under 1080P@60Hz with certain conditions, like open space/horizontal height of equipment, etc</li>\r\n	<li>Support HDCP1.4,compatible with HDCP2.2 Blu-Ray player, follow the output HDCP. But there will be no image if the sink is decrypted.</li>\r\n	<li>Support 100-230V voltage input, DC5V power supply</li>\r\n	<li>Support Many to one(7 TX max to 1 RX), One to many(1 TX to 2 RX max)</li>\r\n	<li>Reset and pairing button for both TX and RX</li>\r\n	<li>No Latency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:456px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:107.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Operating Temperature Range</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:233.95pt\">\r\n			<p>0 to +40℃(+32 to +104℉)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:107.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Operating Humidity Range</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:233.95pt\">\r\n			<p>10 to 90%RH (No Condensation)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:107.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Connectors on Transmitter</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:233.95pt\">\r\n			<p>HDMI Receptacle x 1</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Power USB x 1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:107.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Connectors on Receiver</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:233.95pt\">\r\n			<p>HDMI Receptacle x 1</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Power USB x 1<